AS PART OF BEING HUMAN,

674
00:28:50,999 --> 00:28:54,768
THAT YOU CAN'T HAVE WHAT
YOU WANT WHEN YOU WANT IT.

675
00:28:54,792 --> 00:28:57,810
THE GIRLS WHO HAVEN'T LEARNED
THAT... AND THE BOYS...

676
00:28:57,834 --> 00:29:00,310
ARE IMPULSIVE AND
THEY NEVER CONNECT

677
00:29:00,334 --> 00:29:03,435
WHAT THEY ARE DOING TODAY
WITH WHAT HAPPENS TOMORROW.

678
00:29:03,459 --> 00:29:06,268
NOW, IF THIS BECOMES STYLE
FIVE YEARS FROM NOW,

679
00:29:06,292 --> 00:29:07,975
THAT'S SOMETHING ELSE.

680
00:29:07,999 --> 00:29:11,226
BUT RIGHT NOW, FOR FORMAL
WEAR, IT IS NOT STYLE.

681
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:14,685
IT'S STYLE FOR A VERY SMALL
PERCENTAGE OF PEOPLE.

682
00:29:14,709 --> 00:29:18,975
AND WE'RE GOING TO DO IN THIS
SCHOOL WHAT THE MAJORITY WANTS.

683
00:29:18,999 --> 00:29:23,975
UNTIL THIS KIND OF RULE CHANGES,
THIS IS WHAT WE'RE GOING TO DO.

684
00:29:23,999 --> 00:29:26,059
THE MAJORITY WANTS
A FORMAL AFFAIR,

685
00:29:26,083 --> 00:29:29,059
WHICH MEANS A LONG GOWN OR
A COCKTAIL-LENGTH GOWN.

686
00:29:29,083 --> 00:29:30,643
Boy: THE MAJORITY OF STUDENTS?

687
00:29:30,667 --> 00:29:32,059
THAT'S RIGHT.

688
00:29:32,083 --> 00:29:34,059
Girl: EXCUSE ME, WHAT'S
THE COCKTAIL LENGTH?

689
00:29:34,083 --> 00:29:35,435
Counselor: KNEE LENGTH.

690
00:29:35,459 --> 00:29:36,975
Girl: HERE?

691
00:29:36,999 --> 00:29:38,975
Woman: THE KNEE IS
NOT ABOVE THE KNEE.

692
00:29:38,999 --> 00:29:40,310
Girl: THIS IS MY KNEE.

693
00:29:40,334 --> 00:29:41,975
Woman: NO, IT ISN'T.

694
00:29:41,999 --> 00:29:43,975
IF YOU FELL ON THAT
PART OF YOUR ANATOMY,

695
00:29:43,999 --> 00:29:45,975
YOU WOULD NOT INJURE
YOUR UPPER THIGH.

696
00:29:45,999 --> 00:29:47,768
Counselor: WOULDN'T
TEAR THE DRESS, ANYWAY.

697
00:29:47,792 --> 00:29:49,477
[ WOMAN LAUGHS ]

698
00:29:49,501 --> 00:29:53,894
Counselor: NO, I THINK THAT IT'S
NICE TO BE INDIVIDUALISTIC,

699
00:29:53,918 --> 00:29:57,477
BUT THERE ARE CERTAIN PLACES
TO BE INDIVIDUALISTIC.

700
00:29:57,501 --> 00:29:59,477
Girl: I DIDN'T MEAN TO
BE INDIVIDUALISTIC.

701
00:29:59,501 --> 00:30:01,143
Counselor: NO, I'M
NOT CRITICIZING,

702
00:30:01,167 --> 00:30:02,643
I SAY IT'S NICE TO BE THAT WAY,

703
00:30:02,667 --> 00:30:04,810
BUT THERE ARE CERTAIN
TIMES TO BE THAT WAY.

704
00:30:04,834 --> 00:30:07,768
UH, I THINK YOU CAN BE
INDIVIDUALISTIC IN YOUR DRESS,

705
00:30:07,792 --> 00:30:11,435
BUT IT DOESN'T HAVE TO BE...

706
00:30:11,459 --> 00:30:13,727
Girl: I HAPPEN TO
ENJOY A SHORT GOWN.

707
00:30:13,751 --> 00:30:16,310
I DIDN'T KNOW IT WOULDN'T
BE ACCEPTED TO THE PROM.

708
00:30:16,334 --> 00:30:18,602
I DIDN'T DO IT PURPOSELY
THIS IS WHAT I ENJOY.

709
00:30:18,626 --> 00:30:20,226
Counselor: WHAT
DOES FORMAL MEAN?

710
00:30:20,250 --> 00:30:22,976
Girl: WELL, FORMAL MEANS DRESSY.
I DIDN'T THINK OF IT AS A GOWN.

711
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,560
Counselor: OH.

712
00:30:24,584 --> 00:30:26,560
Woman: FORMAL MEANS
MORE THAN DRESSY.

713
00:30:26,584 --> 00:30:28,727
Counselor: WHEN YOU
GET AN INVITATION

714
00:30:28,751 --> 00:30:29,894
TO A FORMAL AFFAIR,

715
00:30:29,918 --> 00:30:31,852
IT SAYS "WHITE TIE
OR BLACK TIE."

716
00:30:31,876 --> 00:30:33,975
IT DOESN'T SAY THAT THE
GIRLS OR WOMEN WEAR

717
00:30:33,999 --> 00:30:35,685
ANY LENGTH THEY WANT.

718
00:30:35,709 --> 00:30:37,393
IT MEANS A FLOOR-LENGTH GOWN.

719
00:30:37,417 --> 00:30:39,975
YOU GET AN INVITATION
TO A COCKTAIL PARTY,

720
00:30:39,999 --> 00:30:41,975
IT DOESN'T MEAN A
FLOOR-LENGTH GOWN,

721
00:30:41,999 --> 00:30:44,852
IT MEANS A KNEE-LENGTH
GOWN OR A FLOOR-LENGTH.

722
00:30:44,876 --> 00:30:47,975
BUT "FORMAL" MEANS A LONG
GOWN FOR A YOUNG LADY,

723
00:30:47,999 --> 00:30:50,685
A MIDDLE-AGED LADY,
ELDERLY LADY.

724
00:30:50,709 --> 00:30:53,560
SEE WHAT I MEAN, AND FOR
A MAN IT MEANS A TUX,

725
00:30:53,584 --> 00:30:55,560
AND IT'S DETERMINED
BY THE TIME OF DAY

726
00:30:55,584 --> 00:30:57,518
WHETHER IT'S WHITE
TIE OR BLACK TIE.

727
00:30:57,542 --> 00:30:58,975
THERE ARE NO QUESTIONS.

728
00:30:58,999 --> 00:31:00,810
I DIDN'T KNOW ANY OTHER,
REALLY, WHOLE STORY.

729
00:31:00,834 --> 00:31:02,518
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT THEY
WEREN'T PERMITTED.

730
00:31:02,542 --> 00:31:03,976
THIS IS WHAT I
FELT LIKE WEARING.

731
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:05,477
Counselor: IT DOESN'T MATTER

732
00:31:05,501 --> 00:31:07,059
IF IT'S NOT PERMITTED,
IT'S A MATTER

733
00:31:07,083 --> 00:31:08,894
OF WHAT YOU'RE GOING TO DO
IN A SITUATION LIKE THIS.

734
00:31:08,918 --> 00:31:10,393
THIS IS OFFENSIVE
TO THE WHOLE CLASS.

735
00:31:10,417 --> 00:31:11,975
Girl: I DIDN'T REALLY
MEAN IT TO BE.

736
00:31:11,999 --> 00:31:13,975
Counselor: I KNOW YOU PROBABLY
DIDN'T MEAN IT TO BE THIS,

737
00:31:13,999 --> 00:31:15,393
BUT THIS IS WHAT IT IS.

738
00:31:15,417 --> 00:31:16,975
Woman: WE BOUGHT AN ATMOSPHERE

739
00:31:16,999 --> 00:31:18,975
BY RENTING THE SHERATON
BALLROOM, WHICH IS VERY FORMAL.

740
00:31:18,999 --> 00:31:20,852
Counselor: WE COULD HAVE
HAD THE DANCE IN THE GYM.

741
00:31:20,876 --> 00:31:22,768
Woman: WE COULD HAVE
HAD THAT IN THE GYM

742
00:31:22,792 --> 00:31:24,685
AND THEN IT WOULD HAVE BEEN
A LITTLE BIT DIFFERENT.

743
00:31:24,709 --> 00:31:26,643
Counselor: MAYBE A COUPLE OF
GO-GO GIRLS UP ON THE STAGE

744
00:31:26,667 --> 00:31:28,393
WITH A $50 ORCHESTRA,

745
00:31:28,417 --> 00:31:31,018
AND WE WOULD HAVE
HAD A NICE DANCE,

746
00:31:31,042 --> 00:31:32,976
BUT THIS IS NOT JUST A DANCE.

747
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,560
THIS IS THE SENIOR PROM.

748
00:31:34,584 --> 00:31:36,268
THIS IS FORMAL.

749
00:31:36,292 --> 00:31:39,477
IT'S THE ONE TIME IN YOUR LIFE

750
00:31:39,501 --> 00:31:41,894
THAT YOUR CLASS
LOOKS SO DIFFERENT

751
00:31:41,918 --> 00:31:42,894
YOU DON'T RECOGNIZE ANYBODY.

752
00:31:42,918 --> 00:31:44,560
IT'S THE FIRST CHANCE YOU HAVE

753
00:31:44,584 --> 00:31:46,560
TO BE YOUNG LADIES
AND YOUNG GENTLEMEN.

754
00:31:46,584 --> 00:31:49,894
Woman: I HAD A BOY ASK, AND I
HAD A GIRL COME UP AND SAY,

755
00:31:49,918 --> 00:31:52,975
"CAN MY BOYFRIEND WEAR
A DARK SUIT BECAUSE

756
00:31:52,999 --> 00:31:55,643
HE CANNOT AFFORD THE MONEY
FOR THE RENTAL OF A TUX?"

757
00:31:55,667 --> 00:31:57,268
I SAID, "NO, HE CAN'T."

758
00:31:57,292 --> 00:31:58,975
BECAUSE THEN MY HUSBAND
HAS A RIGHT TO WEAR

759
00:31:58,999 --> 00:32:00,975
THE BEAUTIFUL SUIT
HE JUST BOUGHT...

760
00:32:00,999 --> 00:32:03,560
BUT WE HAVE TO PAY, WHAT IS
IT, $10 OR $15 TO RENT A TUX.

761
00:32:03,584 --> 00:32:05,975
NOW, MY HUSBAND HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH THE SCHOOL,

762
00:32:05,999 --> 00:32:10,143
BUT HE'S HONORING THE YOUNGSTERS
BY COMING DRESSED PROPERLY.

763
00:32:10,167 --> 00:32:12,602
Counselor: AND I WOULDN'T THINK
OF COMING WITHOUT WEARING A TUX.

764
00:32:12,626 --> 00:32:14,018
I RENT ONE EVERY YEAR.

765
00:32:14,042 --> 00:32:16,018
Woman: I HAVE TO WEAR A
LONG GOWN, I'D LOVE TO...

766
00:32:16,042 --> 00:32:17,685
AND I CAN'T WALK IN IT.

767
00:32:17,709 --> 00:32:19,976
I CAN'T GET INTO THE
CAR COMFORTABLY.

768
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:26,685
Woman: 5, 6, 7, 8, 9.

769
00:32:26,709 --> 00:32:29,185
OH, BOY, WE'RE FEMININE.
LET'S GO.

770
00:32:29,209 --> 00:32:34,975
4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9.

771
00:32:34,999 --> 00:32:36,185
TARZAN.

772
00:32:36,209 --> 00:32:37,768
1, 2...

773
00:32:37,792 --> 00:32:41,560
3, 4, 5...

774
00:32:41,584 --> 00:32:45,727
6, 7, 8, 9, SUPER TARZAN.

775
00:32:45,751 --> 00:32:50,477
1, 2, 3, 4...

776
00:32:50,501 --> 00:32:54,250
5, 6, 7, 8...

777
00:32:58,667 --> 00:33:01,810
THE DARK FELLOW
HERE IS PAUL SIMON,

778
00:33:01,834 --> 00:33:05,727
AND THE BLOND IS ART GARFUNKEL.

779
00:33:05,751 --> 00:33:09,975
THE POET IS SIMON.

780
00:33:09,999 --> 00:33:12,143
AND IF YOU DOUBT THAT
HE'S A POET NOW,

781
00:33:12,167 --> 00:33:14,226
WAIT UNTIL YOU HEAR
SOME OF HIS POETRY.

782
00:33:14,250 --> 00:33:16,768
AND YOU'LL NOTICE ON THE
BOARD I HAVE SOME THINGS

783
00:33:16,792 --> 00:33:18,975
THAT YOU'RE FAMILIAR
WITH... IMAGES, SETTING,

784
00:33:18,999 --> 00:33:20,810
FIGURATIVE LANGUAGE,
THEMATIC WORDS.

785
00:33:20,834 --> 00:33:25,143
AND WE'LL BE FINDING HOW
HE SAYS WHAT HE DOES SAY.

786
00:33:25,167 --> 00:33:28,435
WHAT DO THEY WANT TO SAY
ABOUT OUR LIVES AND HOW?

787
00:33:28,459 --> 00:33:32,435
AND I THINK THE BEST WAY
TO START IS BY LOOKING

788
00:33:32,459 --> 00:33:35,975
AT ONE OF THE BEST OF THE POEMS,
"THE DANGLING CONVERSATION."

789
00:33:35,999 --> 00:33:38,852
THAT'S THE FIRST
ONE ON YOUR SHEET.

790
00:33:38,876 --> 00:33:42,059
THE PROCESS WE'LL USE...
FIRST, WE'LL READ THE POEM,

791
00:33:42,083 --> 00:33:44,976
THEN LISTEN TO IT, THEN
WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT

792
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:48,435
AND SEE HOW ALL THE
VARIOUS POETIC DEVICES

793
00:33:48,459 --> 00:33:51,975
REINFORCE THE THEME, AND SEE
WHAT YOU THINK ABOUT IT,

794
00:33:51,999 --> 00:33:53,975
AND THEN WE'LL LISTEN
TO IT ONCE AGAIN,

795
00:33:53,999 --> 00:33:58,975
AND I'LL BET IT MEANS SOMETHING
A LITTLE BIT MORE TO YOU.

796
00:33:58,999 --> 00:34:02,518
"IT'S A STILL-LIFE WATERCOLOR
OF THE NOW-LATE AFTERNOON,

797
00:34:02,542 --> 00:34:04,975
"AS THE SUN SHINES
THROUGH THE CURTAIN LACE

798
00:34:04,999 --> 00:34:07,560
"AND SHADOWS WASH THE ROOM.

799
00:34:07,584 --> 00:34:10,351
"AND WE SIT AND
DRINK OUR COFFEE,

800
00:34:10,375 --> 00:34:12,143
"COUCHED IN OUR INDIFFERENCE,

801
00:34:12,167 --> 00:34:14,101
"LIKE SHELLS UPON THE SHORE,

802
00:34:14,125 --> 00:34:16,101
"YOU CAN HEAR THE OCEAN ROAR,

803
00:34:16,125 --> 00:34:19,975
"IN THE DANGLING CONVERSATION
AND THE SUPERFICIAL SIGHS,

804
00:34:19,998 --> 00:34:22,435
"THE BORDERS OF OUR LIVES.

805
00:34:22,458 --> 00:34:24,601
"AND YOU READ YOUR
EMILY DICKINSON

806
00:34:24,626 --> 00:34:26,685
"AND I MY ROBERT FROST,

807
00:34:26,708 --> 00:34:28,685
"AND WE NOTE OUR PLACE
WITH BOOKMARKERS

808
00:34:28,708 --> 00:34:30,975
"AND MEASURE WHAT WE LOST,

809
00:34:30,998 --> 00:34:34,975
"LIKE A POEM POORLY WRITTEN,
WE ARE VERSES OUT OF RHYTHM,

810
00:34:34,998 --> 00:34:38,726
"COUPLETS OUT OF RHYME,
IN SYNCOPATED TIME.

811
00:34:38,751 --> 00:34:42,560
"AND THE DANGLING CONVERSATION
AND THE SUPERFICIAL SIGHS

812
00:34:42,583 --> 00:34:44,975
"ARE THE BORDERS OF OUR LIVES.

813
00:34:44,998 --> 00:34:47,975
"YES, WE SPEAK THE
THINGS THAT MATTER

814
00:34:47,998 --> 00:34:50,310
"WITH WORDS THAT MUST BE SAID...

815
00:34:50,333 --> 00:34:52,310
"CAN ANALYSIS BE WORTHWHILE?

816
00:34:52,333 --> 00:34:54,685
"IS THE THEATER REALLY DEAD?

817
00:34:54,708 --> 00:34:56,976
"AND HOW THE ROOM
IS SOFTLY FADED,

818
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:58,975
"AS I ONLY KISS YOUR SHADOW,

819
00:34:58,999 --> 00:35:01,310
"I CANNOT FEEL YOUR HAND,

820
00:35:01,334 --> 00:35:04,685
"YOU'RE A STRANGER
NOW UNTO ME, LOST,

821
00:35:04,709 --> 00:35:07,975
"IN THE DANGLING CONVERSATION
AND THE SUPERFICIAL SIGHS,

822
00:35:07,999 --> 00:35:10,185
THE BORDERS OF OUR LIVES."

823
00:35:10,209 --> 00:35:12,185
LET'S LISTEN TO IT.

824
00:35:12,209 --> 00:35:15,018
AND NOTICE HOW NOT
ONLY THE DEVICES

825
00:35:15,042 --> 00:35:16,810
REINFORCE THE THEME

826
00:35:16,834 --> 00:35:20,477
BUT ALSO THE VERY
RHYTHMS, THE MELODIES,

827
00:35:20,501 --> 00:35:22,518
AND HOW THEY USED THEIR TIMING.

828
00:35:22,542 --> 00:35:24,101
NOW, WHEN I TAPED THESE,

829
00:35:24,125 --> 00:35:27,852
THEY WERE FROM A MONAURAL
AND STEREO RECORDS.

830
00:35:27,876 --> 00:35:29,852
THE TAPE IS A LITTLE FAST...

831
00:35:29,876 --> 00:35:31,975
IT'S THE DRAMA CLUB
TAPE RECORDER,

832
00:35:31,999 --> 00:35:35,042
SO YOU'LL HAVE TO BE A LITTLE
PATIENT AT THE VERY BEGINNING.

833
00:35:38,999 --> 00:35:40,501
[ SONG BEGINS ]

