00:38:49,250 --> 00:38:51,268
FOR THROWING THE FIRST
PUNCH... YES, SIR.

889
00:38:51,292 --> 00:38:53,268
DON'T GIVE ME THAT
"YES, SIR" BUSINESS.

890
00:38:53,292 --> 00:38:55,727
I DON'T LIKE THE "SIR" BUSINESS.
YOU KNOW WHY?

891
00:38:55,751 --> 00:38:58,727
BECAUSE THERE'S NO
SINCERENESS BEHIND IT.

892
00:38:58,751 --> 00:39:02,059
Female dean: AND HOW ABOUT
THE POOR, POOR TEACHER,

893
00:39:02,083 --> 00:39:03,975
WHOEVER IT WAS?

894
00:39:03,999 --> 00:39:05,975
I DON'T KNOW.

895
00:39:05,999 --> 00:39:08,894
Girl: I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT
SHE SAID THAT WE DID, BUT...

896
00:39:08,918 --> 00:39:10,393
Dean: IT'S A MATTER OF

897
00:39:10,417 --> 00:39:12,393
BEING INHUMAN TO
ANOTHER HUMAN BEING.

898
00:39:12,417 --> 00:39:14,477
THAT'S WHAT IT AMOUNTS TO.

899
00:39:14,501 --> 00:39:17,518
Girl: BUT ALL I KNOW
IS THAT SHE GOT SUE

900
00:39:17,542 --> 00:39:18,894
IN A LOT OF TROUBLE AND...

901
00:39:18,918 --> 00:39:20,975
Dean: SUE WHO?

902
00:39:20,999 --> 00:39:22,685
Girl: THE OTHER GIRL.

903
00:39:22,709 --> 00:39:24,975
AND SUE DIDN'T... I DON'T
THINK SUE HAD ANY...

904
00:39:24,999 --> 00:39:28,477
SHE TOLD... SHE SAID THAT WE
LOCKED HER IN THE CLOSET.

905
00:39:28,501 --> 00:39:31,185
Dean: YOU MEAN SUE AND YOU?

906
00:39:31,209 --> 00:39:34,059
Girl: I MEAN THE CLASS.

907
00:39:34,083 --> 00:39:36,393
NOBODY LOCKED HER IN THE
CLOSET AS FAR AS I KNOW.

908
00:39:36,417 --> 00:39:38,602
LOOK, IF SHE WOULD'VE BEEN
LOCKED IN THE CLOSET,

909
00:39:38,626 --> 00:39:42,435
I SURE WOULD HAVE HEARD THAT
AND TURNED AROUND AND LOOKED.

910
00:39:42,459 --> 00:39:45,059
Dean: SHE MAY HAVE HAD A
LITTLE MORE CONTROL THAN THAT.

911
00:39:45,083 --> 00:39:47,477
THAT MUCH NOISE, IT'S A
LITTLE EMBARRASSING TO HER.

912
00:39:47,501 --> 00:39:49,518
SHE WASN'T GOING TO CALL
EVERYBODY'S ATTENTION TO IT.

913
00:39:49,542 --> 00:39:50,975
Girl: IT WASN'T FAIR.

914
00:39:50,999 --> 00:39:54,976
SUE WAS JUST MESSING AROUND,
JUST AS MUCH AS US.

915
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:57,393
THE REST OF THE CLASS...

916
00:39:57,417 --> 00:39:59,018
AND NOW SUE'S IN
SO MUCH TROUBLE,

917
00:39:59,042 --> 00:40:00,975
JUST BECAUSE OF
THAT ONE TEACHER.

918
00:40:00,999 --> 00:40:03,518
AND BECAUSE SUE GOT IN TROUBLE,
I BLAME IT A LOT ON THE TEACHER

919
00:40:03,542 --> 00:40:05,226
'CAUSE...

920
00:40:05,250 --> 00:40:08,602
Dean: WELL, LET'S KEEP LOOKING
AT THAT BECAUSE, AGAIN,

921
00:40:08,626 --> 00:40:11,226
THIS IS MY CONCERN, EILEEN.

922
00:40:11,250 --> 00:40:13,975
SUE GOT IN TROUBLE
BECAUSE OF THE TEACHER.

923
00:40:13,999 --> 00:40:15,852
SUE DID NOTHING TO HELP?

924
00:40:15,876 --> 00:40:17,393
WHOEVER SUE IS, I DON'T KNOW.

925
00:40:17,417 --> 00:40:19,393
I'M GLAD YOU DIDN'T ANSWER
WHEN I ASKED YOU HER NAME

926
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:21,518
BECAUSE IT'S EASIER TO TALK.

927
00:40:21,542 --> 00:40:23,059
Eileen: SHE JUST MESSED
AROUND LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE.

928
00:40:23,083 --> 00:40:25,518
Woman: LOOK, CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT "MESSING AROUND" MEANS?

929
00:40:25,542 --> 00:40:27,810
THIS IS WHAT I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO FIND OUT FOR MONTHS.

930
00:40:27,834 --> 00:40:29,852
EVERY TIME YOU WOULD
SAY "MESSING AROUND."

931
00:40:29,876 --> 00:40:32,975
WHAT DOES IT
ACTUALLY CONSIST OF?

932
00:40:32,999 --> 00:40:36,477
Eileen: I DON'T KNOW, WE
WERE TALKING, LAUGHING...

933
00:40:36,501 --> 00:40:42,101
WELL, JUST PLAIN TALKING AND
LAUGHING ISN'T OFFENSIVE.

934
00:40:42,125 --> 00:40:45,975
Eileen: WELL, WE WERE
CATCHING A BOOK OR SOMETHING.

935
00:40:45,999 --> 00:40:47,975
OH, YOU THREW A BOOK AROUND?

936
00:40:47,999 --> 00:40:49,852
Eileen: NOT JUST ME!

937
00:40:49,876 --> 00:40:52,143
BUT WHOEVER WAS INVOLVED.

938
00:40:52,167 --> 00:40:53,975
Eileen: I KNOW I DID A LOT.

939
00:40:53,999 --> 00:40:56,643
LIKE, I DID A LOT. I
TALKED BACK A LOT.

940
00:40:56,667 --> 00:40:58,768
DID YOU TALK BACK
TO THE TEACHER?

941
00:40:58,792 --> 00:40:59,959
Eileen: YEAH.

942
00:41:01,626 --> 00:41:04,268
AND THIS IS WHAT YOU
CALL "MESSING AROUND"?

943
00:41:04,292 --> 00:41:06,101
Eileen: NO, WELL...

944
00:41:06,125 --> 00:41:08,393
ISN'T THAT MORE DISRESPECT?

945
00:41:08,417 --> 00:41:11,852
Eileen: WHAT I DID WAS
DISRESPECT, BUT WHAT THE REST...

946
00:41:11,876 --> 00:41:16,975
WHAT EVERYBODY ELSE DID
WAS MESSING AROUND.

947
00:41:16,999 --> 00:41:18,477
I DON'T... I DON'T KNOW.

948
00:41:18,501 --> 00:41:20,351
Dean: YOU SEE, WHAT
MOTHER IS SAYING...

949
00:41:20,375 --> 00:41:22,351
AT LEAST WHAT I'M SAYING, I
THINK WHAT MOTHER IS SAYING...

950
00:41:22,375 --> 00:41:23,975
IS THAT WE HOPE, EILEEN,

951
00:41:23,999 --> 00:41:25,685
THAT YOU DON'T SET
YOUR STANDARDS BY

952
00:41:25,709 --> 00:41:27,310
THE SO-CALLED "EVERYBODY ELSE,"

953
00:41:27,334 --> 00:41:28,935
THAT YOU SET YOUR STANDARDS

954
00:41:28,959 --> 00:41:33,768
ON WHAT YOU KNOW IS
THE THING TO DO.

955
00:41:33,792 --> 00:41:36,935
I REPEAT, THERE'S NO DOUBT

956
00:41:36,959 --> 00:41:39,727
THE TEACHER WAS NOT
HOLDING THE CLASS,

957
00:41:39,751 --> 00:41:42,685
WAS NOT DOING THE JOB YOU
THINK SHE SHOULD HAVE DONE,

958
00:41:42,709 --> 00:41:45,351
FROM WHAT YOU SAY,
I'LL ACCEPT THAT.

959
00:41:45,375 --> 00:41:48,477
BUT WHO BREAKS THE CIRCLE

960
00:41:48,501 --> 00:41:50,685
WHEN THINGS GO AROUND
AND AROUND AND AROUND?

961
00:41:50,709 --> 00:41:52,685
SOMEONE HAS TO BE MATURE ENOUGH

962
00:41:52,709 --> 00:41:54,975
TO MOVE OUT OF THE CIRCLE AND
INTO THE STRAIGHT, RIGHT?

963
00:41:54,999 --> 00:41:58,976
SOMEBODY HAS GOT TO
BREAK AWAY FROM IT.

964
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:02,435
YOU'RE INTELLIGENT,
YOU'RE MATURE,

965
00:42:02,459 --> 00:42:03,975
YOU HAVE THE BACKGROUND.

966
00:42:03,999 --> 00:42:05,999
YOU CAN BE THE ONE
THAT CAN DO IT.

967
00:42:08,542 --> 00:42:13,643
WHY DON'T YOU OFFER THE POSITIVE
KIND OF LEADERSHIP THAT YOU CAN,

968
00:42:13,667 --> 00:42:15,643
THAT YOU KNOW YOU HAVE AND
THAT I KNOW YOU HAVE,

969
00:42:15,667 --> 00:42:17,518
THAT MOTHER KNOWS YOU HAVE?

970
00:42:17,542 --> 00:42:20,768
YOU CAN BE A REAL FORCE
IN ANY GROUP, EILEEN.

971
00:42:20,792 --> 00:42:22,685
CAN'T YOU?

972
00:42:22,709 --> 00:42:24,975
THE KIDS RALLY AROUND YOU A BIT.

973
00:42:24,999 --> 00:42:27,727
Eileen: WELL, NOT REALLY.

974
00:42:27,751 --> 00:42:30,518
I'VE SEEN YOU IN THE LUNCHROOM.

975
00:42:30,542 --> 00:42:32,518
WE'VE GOT US A POTENTIAL LEADER.

976
00:42:32,542 --> 00:42:33,975
Mother: EILEEN CAN.

977
00:42:33,999 --> 00:42:35,602
Dean: IT SHOWS WHEREVER SHE IS.

978
00:42:35,626 --> 00:42:37,435
I'VE SEEN HER ONCE IN
A WHILE IN A GROUP.

979
00:42:37,459 --> 00:42:39,894
YOU CAN SEE WHO THE LEADER IS
IN A GROUP, AND SHE HAS IT.

980
00:42:39,918 --> 00:42:42,975
EILEEN HAS A VERY SET MIND,

981
00:42:42,999 --> 00:42:45,685
AND IF SHE DECIDES THAT
SOMETHING SHOULD BE DONE,

982
00:42:45,709 --> 00:42:47,975
THIS IS WHAT SHE PURSUES,
THIS I KNOW ABOUT HER.

983
00:42:47,999 --> 00:42:49,101
Dean: I THINK THAT'S GOOD.

984
00:42:49,125 --> 00:42:51,393
I THINK IT'S EXCELLENT
IN MANY WAYS,

985
00:42:51,417 --> 00:42:52,975
BUT I'VE OFTEN SAID TO HER,

986
00:42:52,999 --> 00:42:55,727
"EILEEN, USE YOUR
DETERMINATION FOR RIGHT.

987
00:42:55,751 --> 00:42:58,602
AND AS LONG AS YOU DO,
YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT."

988
00:42:58,626 --> 00:43:01,975
AND ONE THING, THIS IS THE ONE
THING THAT BOTHERS ME SO MUCH...

989
00:43:01,999 --> 00:43:04,685
THE MAIN THING IN OUR
HOME HAS ALWAYS BEEN

990
00:43:04,709 --> 00:43:06,727
RESPECT FOR AN ADULT.

991
00:43:06,751 --> 00:43:09,310
I WAS BROUGHT UP THAT
WAY... MY HUSBAND WAS.

992
00:43:09,334 --> 00:43:12,185
AND WE HAVE BEEN TRYING TO TEACH
OUR CHILDREN THE SAME THING.

993
00:43:12,209 --> 00:43:14,975
TO ME, I THINK, ONE
OF THE WORST OFFENSES

994
00:43:14,999 --> 00:43:18,518
IS BEING DISRESPECTFUL
TO AN OLDER PERSON.

995
00:43:18,542 --> 00:43:20,976
IRREGARDLESS OF WHAT
THE CONDITION MAY BE.

996
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:23,935
YOU CAN SAY THE SAME THING
IN A PLEASANT MANNER

997
00:43:23,959 --> 00:43:26,560
THAT YOU CAN IN
AN OFFENSIVE WAY.

998
00:43:26,584 --> 00:43:28,143
AND THIS IS ONE THING

999
00:43:28,167 --> 00:43:30,393
THAT'S DISTURBED ME
RECENTLY ABOUT EILEEN.

1000
00:43:30,417 --> 00:43:32,310
THAT EVEN AT HOME, NOW SHE...

1001
00:43:32,334 --> 00:43:35,143
I DON'T SAY THE LANGUAGE
THAT SHE USES IS WRONG,

1002
00:43:35,167 --> 00:43:38,101
BUT IT'S THE MANNER
THAT THE SAME...

1003
00:43:38,125 --> 00:43:40,059
THAT A SENTENCE
IS BROUGHT FORTH.

1004
00:43:40,083 --> 00:43:42,975
AND I TOLD HER,
"EVENTUALLY, EILEEN,

1005
00:43:42,999 --> 00:43:45,185
THIS IS GOING TO
HURT YOU OUTSIDE."

1006
00:43:45,209 --> 00:43:47,976
AND FINALLY IT HAS.

1007
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:51,059
AND I THINK YOU WOULD KIND
OF HAVE TO DECIDE, ARLEEN,

1008
00:43:51,083 --> 00:43:54,727
HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT WHERE YOU
STOOD IN YOUR COLLEGE CLASS,

1009
00:43:54,751 --> 00:43:56,685
WHETHER YOU WOULD RATHER
BE IN AN EASIER SCHOOL,

1010
00:43:56,709 --> 00:43:58,602
AND TOWARD THE TOP OF THE CLASS,

1011
00:43:58,626 --> 00:44:00,351
OR IN A HARDER SCHOOL

1012
00:44:00,375 --> 00:44:03,393
AND TOWARD THE
BOTTOM OF THE CLASS.

1013
00:44:03,417 --> 00:44:04,975
I THINK I WOULD GAIN
MORE BY BEING, LIKE,

1014
00:44:04,999 --> 00:44:07,477
IN THE MIDDLE OR THE TOP THAN
BEING AT THE VERY BOTTOM,

1015
00:44:07,501 --> 00:44:11,018
NOT BEING ABLE TO KEEP
UP WITH EVERYBODY ELSE.

1016
00:44:11,042 --> 00:44:13,560
Counselor: DO YOU WANT A
COLLEGE COURSE, THEN, DEAR,

1017
00:44:13,584 --> 00:44:16,477
WHERE, AT THE END OF FOUR
YEARS, YOU WOULD BE FINISHED

1018
00:44:16,501 --> 00:44:19,560
WITH YOUR EDUCATION AND ABLE
TO GO OUT AND MAKE A LIVING,

1019
00:44:19,584 --> 00:44:22,643
OR DO YOU WANT THE KIND OF
COURSE WHERE, AT THE END

1020
00:44:22,667 --> 00:44:24,477
OF FOUR YEARS, IT IS
LIKELY THAT YOU WOULD BE

1021
00:44:24,501 --> 00:44:26,894
GOING ON WITH YOUR EDUCATION?

1022
00:44:26,918 --> 00:44:28,768
Arleen: I'M NOT SURE RIGHT NOW.

1023
00:44:28,792 --> 00:44:30,975
I THINK I WANT TO GO TO
FOUR YEARS OF COLLEGE

1024
00:44:30,999 --> 00:44:32,852
AND, MAYBE, IF I
BECOME A TEACHER,

1025
00:44:32,876 --> 00:44:34,894
STOP, AND THEN I CAN
ALWAYS TAKE COURSES AGAIN,

1026
00:44:34,918 --> 00:44:39,560
GO HIGHER, GET A HIGHER DEGREE.

1027
00:44:39,584 --> 00:44:43,143
OR, I THINK, UH, A SOCIAL WORKER

1028
00:44:43,167 --> 00:44:44,727
OR PSYCHOLOGIST HAS
TO GO FIVE YEARS.

1029
00:44:44,751 --> 00:44:46,727
Counselor: OR SIX
YEARS OR SEVEN YEARS.

1030
00:44:46,751 --> 00:44:49,435
IT WOULD DEPEND ON WHAT
YOU CHOSE AFTER THAT.

1031
00:44:49,459 --> 00:44:51,435
I DON'T THINK I WANT
TO GO MORE THAN

1032
00:44:51,459 --> 00:44:54,975
MAYBE FIVE OR SIX YEARS,
OR MORE THAN FIVE.

1033
00:44:54,999 --> 00:44:57,602
WELL, I THINK YOU'VE GIVEN ME

1034
00:44:57,626 --> 00:45:00,435
A PRETTY COMPREHENSIVE IDEA
OF WHAT YOU ARE LOOKING FOR.

1035
00:45:00,459 --> 00:45:02,685
AND THEN I WOULD HAVE
TO ASK YOU, SIR,

1036
00:45:02,709 --> 00:45:04,976
THE HARD, HARD
QUESTION OF HOW MUCH

1037
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:07,602
COULD YOU CONTRIBUTE TO
YOUR DAUGHTER'S EDUCATION?

1038
00:45:07,626 --> 00:45:10,310
Father: WELL, UH,
THAT'S A HARD QUESTION

1039
00:45:10,334 --> 00:45:13,018
TO SAY BECAUSE, UH, IF SHE
LIVES AWAY FROM HOME,

1040
00:45:13,042 --> 00:45:14,768
THEN IT'S A DIFFERENT
STORY ALTOGETHER.

1041
00:45:14,792 --> 00:45:18,101
AND IF SHE IS AT HOME,
IT'S ANOTHER STORY.

1042
00:45:18,125 --> 00:45:21,935
BUT THE WAY SHE'S TALKING, SHE
DOESN'T WANT TO STAY HOME.

1043
00:45:21,959 --> 00:45:25,975
SO I WOULD SAY ABOUT $1,000,
$1,500 IS ABOUT THE BEST

1044
00:45:25,999 --> 00:45:28,975
I COULD GIVE HER A YEAR
TO GO AWAY TO COLLEGE.

1045
00:45:28,999 --> 00:45:30,768
MM-HMM.

1046
00:45:30,792 --> 00:45:32,226
THEN IT WOULD SEEM
TO ME THAT, ARLEEN,

1047
00:45:32,250 --> 00:45:35,018
THAT THE MOST REALISTIC
WAY TO PLAN IT WOULD BE

1048
00:45:35,042 --> 00:45:37,975
TO THINK ABOUT
WHERE YOU COULD GO

1049
00:45:37,999 --> 00:45:43,518
IF YOUR FATHER COULD GIVE
YOU $1,000 TO $1,500,

1050
00:45:43,542 --> 00:45:47,602
AND THEN TO TRY FOR SCHOLARSHIP
IN SOME OTHER PLACES

1051
00:45:47,626 --> 00:45:49,143
THAT MIGHT BE SOMEWHAT
MORE EXPENSIVE.

1052
00:45:49,167 --> 00:45:51,477
BUT, I THINK YOU
KIND OF HAVE TO PLAN

1053
00:45:51,501 --> 00:45:53,226
FOR WHERE YOU WOULD GO

1054
00:45:53,250 --> 00:45:56,351
IF YOU DIDN'T GET ANY
FINANCIAL AID FROM SOMEONE.

1055
00:45:56,375 --> 00:45:58,975
I MEAN, YOU ALWAYS HAVE TO...
YOU LOOK AT THE BRIGHTER SIDE

1056
00:45:58,999 --> 00:46:00,351
ABOUT WHERE YOU
WOULD LIKE TO GO,

1057
00:46:00,375 --> 00:46:01,975
YOU CAN HAVE ALL
YOUR DREAM SCHOOLS,

1058
00:46:01,999 --> 00:46:03,435
BUT AT THE BOTTOM,

1059
00:46:03,459 --> 00:46:05,685
YOU OUGHT TO HAVE SOME
COLLEGE OF LAST RESORT

1060
00:46:05,709 --> 00:46:08,975
WHERE YOU COULD BE SURE
THAT YOU WOULD GO,

1061
00:46:08,999 --> 00:46:12,935
IF NONE OF YOUR
DREAMS CAME TRUE.

1062
00:46:12,959 --> 00:46:16,975
RHONA IS THE RECIPIENT OF A
$10,000 HERO SCHOLARSHIP

1063
00:46:16,999 --> 00:46:20,852
TO ANY COLLEGE ANYWHERE IN
THE COUNTRY SHE WANTS TO GO.

1064
00:46:20,876 --> 00:46:22,975
Father: I'M NOT SAYING
SHE IS COLLEGE MATERIAL,

1065
00:46:22,999 --> 00:46:25,894
BUT AT LEAST SHE CAN HAVE SOME
TYPE OF EDUCATION, FOLLOWING...

1066
00:46:25,918 --> 00:46:27,518
SHE CAN GO TO ANY COLLEGE

1067
00:46:27,542 --> 00:46:28,810
AND DO WHATEVER SHE WANTED.

1068
00:46:28,834 --> 00:46:31,101
TELL ME AGAIN,

1069
00:46:31,125 --> 00:46:33,143
DO YOU THINK YOU WANT
TO GO TO COLLEGE?

1070
00:46:33,167 --> 00:46:35,435
YES.

1071
00:46:35,459 --> 00:46:37,143
Father: PLEASE, NOW,
YOU'RE LYING TO THE MAN...

1072
00:46:37,167 --> 00:46:38,894
YOU DON'T WANT TO GO TO COLLEGE.

1073
00:46:38,918 --> 00:46:40,560
WELL, I DO, BUT NOT
THE KIND OF COLLEGE

1074
00:46:40,584 --> 00:46:41,976
THAT YOU WANT ME TO.

1075
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:43,727
WHAT KIND OF COLLEGE
DO YOU WANT TO GO TO?

1076
00:46:43,751 --> 00:46:45,143
I WANT TO BE A COSMETICIAN.

1077
00:46:45,167 --> 00:46:47,518
COSMETICIAN? BUT THAT'S
NOT A COLLEGE, IS IT?

1078
00:46:47,542 --> 00:46:48,975
WELL, IT'S A BEAUTY
CULTURE SCHOOL.

1079
00:46:48,999 --> 00:46:51,602
IT'S A BEAUTY CULTURE
SCHOOL, IT'S NOT A COLLEGE.

1080
00:46:51,626 --> 00:46:53,560
THE REQUIREMENTS FOR THAT ARE
DIFFERENT THAN FOR COLLEGE.

1081
00:46:53,584 --> 00:46:54,976
YES.

1082
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:57,018
YOU DON'T HAVE ANY
FOREIGN LANGUAGE. NO.

1083
00:46:57,042 --> 00:46:58,602
YOU DON'T HAVE ANY ALGEBRA,

1084
00:46:58,626 --> 00:46:59,975
YOU DON'T HAVE GEOMETRY.

1085
00:46:59,999 --> 00:47:01,975
SO THAT ACTUALLY, AS FAR
AS GOING TO COLLEGE,

1086
00:47:01,999 --> 00:47:04,310
YOU'RE NOT EVEN
PREPARED FOR A COLLEGE.

1087
00:47:04,334 --> 00:47:06,518
DO YOU FEEL THAT YOU ARE
DISAPPOINTING YOUR PARENTS

1088
00:47:06,542 --> 00:47:07,975
BY NOT GOING TO COLLEGE?

1089
00:47:07,999 --> 00:47:09,101
NOW, TELL ME THE TRUTH.

1090
00:47:09,125 --> 00:47:10,518
YES.

1091
00:47:10,542 --> 00:47:11,727
YOU FEEL YOUR PARENTS
ARE DISAPPOINTED?

1092
00:47:11,751 --> 00:47:12,226
MY FATHER.

1093
00:47:12,250 --> 00:47:14,351
YOUR FATHER IS?

1094
00:47:14,375 --> 00:47:16,975
TELL ME, WOULD YOU FEEL BETTER
IF YOU KNEW YOUR FATHER

1095
00:47:16,999 --> 00:47:19,935
REALLY ACCEPTED THE FACT THAT
YOU DIDN'T GO TO COLLEGE?

1096
00:47:19,959 --> 00:47:22,810
YOU FEEL A BIT GUILTY FOR
NOT GOING TO COLLEGE?

1097
00:47:22,834 --> 00:47:24,727
YES, WHAT DO YOU SAY?

1098
00:47:24,751 --> 00:47:25,935
WELL...

1099
00:47:25,959 --> 00:47:27,727
THAT YOU ARE DISAPPOINTING
YOUR PARENTS?

1100
00:47:27,751 --> 00:47:29,768
I'M DISAPPOINTING MY FATHER,

1101
00:47:29,792 --> 00:47:31,975
BUT I DON'T THINK I'D FEEL
GUILTY ABOUT NOT GOING.

1102
00:47:31,999 --> 00:47:33,435
YOU DON'T FEEL GUILTY AT ALL?

